

MODULE M10 — WORKPLACE VIOLENCE & HARASSMENT PREVENTION
5-Minute Lesson Script

INTRODUCTION (20–30 seconds)
“Welcome to Module M10: Workplace Violence and Harassment Prevention.
Your safety matters — and no form of violence, harassment, or intimidation is tolerated at CFM.”

SECTION 1 — WHAT IS WORKPLACE VIOLENCE? (45 seconds)
“Workplace violence includes:
* Verbal threats
* Intimidation
* Aggressive body language
* Physical assault
* The presence of weapons
This applies to patients, visitors, and coworkers.”

SECTION 2 — HARASSMENT & DISCRIMINATION (60 seconds)
“Harassment includes unwanted comments, touching, jokes, advances, or behaviors of a sexual, offensive, or discriminatory nature.
CFM prohibits:
* Sexual harassment
* Racial or religious harassment
* Bullying
* Retaliation for reporting
* Any behavior that creates a hostile work environment”

SECTION 3 — DE-ESCALATION BASICS (45 seconds)
“When someone becomes agitated:
* Stay calm
* Lower your voice
* Give space
* Offer choices instead of demands
* Call for assistance early
Your goal is safety, not winning an argument.”

SECTION 4 — SCENARIO CHECKPOINT (40 seconds)
“Scenario:
A visitor begins pacing, clenching their fists, and speaking loudly at the front desk.
Pause…
What should you do?
Maintain distance, speak calmly, notify leadership immediately, and prepare to call 911 if the behavior escalates.”

CLOSING SUMMARY (30 seconds)
“To summarize:
CFM has zero tolerance for violence or harassment.
Recognize warning signs, de-escalate when possible, and call for help early.
Your safety comes first — always.
When you're ready, take the Module M10 quiz.”

END OF MODULE M10

